BT /F2 15 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54 542.00 Tm (6. Terms You Should Know) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 518.00 Tm (- Props: data passed into a component. Example: AuthHeader receives loggedInEmail.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 502.00 Tm (- State: data a component remembers while the user interacts. Example: letter, loading, error.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 486.00 Tm (- Hooks: React functions like useState, useEffect, useRef, useActionState.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 470.00 Tm (- Routes: URL-based files. app/page.tsx is /; app/api/cover-letter/route.ts is /api/cover-letter.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 454.00 Tm (- API calls: network requests. The cover-letter component calls your own API, and your API calls) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 440.00 Tm (  OpenAI.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 424.00 Tm (- Environment variables: secret/config values like NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 410.00 Tm (  NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 394.00 Tm (- Authentication: proving who the user is. Supabase handles sign up, sign in, sign out, cookies,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 380.00 Tm (  and sessions.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 364.00 Tm (- Database tables: structured storage. This app mainly uses jobs.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 348.00 Tm (- Server components: React components that run on the server. app/page.tsx is one.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 332.00 Tm (- Client components: React components that run in the browser. Files with "use client".) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 316.00 Tm (- Server actions: functions marked "use server" that forms can call securely.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 300.00 Tm (- Middleware: code that runs before page requests; here it refreshes Supabase sessions.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 284.00 Tm (- RLS: Row Level Security. Supabase rules that prevent users from reading/writing other users') Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 66 270.00 Tm (  rows.) Tj ET
